commit_message:
Datapath on L2pop only for agents with tunneling-ip

This patch is a regression issue for patch[1].

Only those agents which expose tunneling-ip will be considered in
determining data-path tunnels in deployments with l2pop ON.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/236970/

Change-Id: I7c3b911d5e7448b4e8dee15bb50df33a6e9d5cfe
Closes-Bug: #1407959

commit_message:
Fix to call logging.setup() once

logging.setup() is called twice when murano-api, murano-engine,
murano-cfapi starts. This patch fixes it to call once.

commit_message:
Remove unused neutron variable definition

Removing neutron_galera_password variable in roles/os_neutron/defaults/main.yml
which has never been used. In fact,  all related password variables are defined in
etc/openstack_deploy/user_secrets.yml.

Change-Id: I460215d4e10f13b1dc3f7504d3914d4e84862adb
(cherry picked from commit 2e9c7d7b0a39a02ae1aa151f1f3b8971ce4c77ae)

Ensure that stacks can't get stuck IN_PROGRESS

Make sure that any unexpected exceptions are handled by moving the stack to
the FAILED state.

Change-Id: Ic948c2fe5baf23c9c4ced33060f672ca9c278a19
Closes-Bug: #1492433
(cherry picked from commit 17b5f9ec84e8ad7f8c2b0f38b599456995d0aa75)

(Please see I372fc1091bbcf1022a4d8d4ae60e65ab67a8e432)

commit_message:
Add support for legacy envvar prefixes

In trying to move the legacy clients to do their config via
os-client-config, many of them had prefixes like NOVA_ or GLANCE_
in their shells. It's pretty easy to support optionally passing those
in so that the transition to OCC is less of a change and we can
treat the deprecation cycle of those features as a different topic.

Change-Id: Ic819c0790989fa034db03d83535ee7b70aaacc3a

commit_message:
Fix name of the object-store api key

There is only one value for this, and it's not consumed in the process
of making a swift client, so the chances that anyone set it
to something else are pretty much nil. However, for completeness we
should make it the right name, as "object-store" is the service key
name for swift, not "object".

Change-Id: I395c1c44a2f50996b61dff22e07149b8dd13eda9

commit_message:
Refactor per-service key making

The key for swift is object-store, but the key in the config dict
would be object_store_api_version, so the key concatenation would
not work. In fixing that, refactor out the creation of the keys so
that the concatenation and transformation needed always happens.

Change-Id: Ic095912bfc84f13ef8b11f312303a517289e0441

commit_message:
xen: mask passwords in volume connection_data dict

The connection_data dict can have credentials in it, so we need to scrub
those before putting the stringified dict into the StorageError message
and raising that up and when logging the dict.

Note that strutils.mask_password converts the dict to a string using
six.text_type so we don't have to do that conversion first.

SecurityImpact

Change-Id: Ic5f4d4c26794550a92481bf2b725ef5eafa581b2
Closes-Bug: #1516765

commit_message:
Add existing_amphorae attribute of LoadBalancer model

This attribute is a list of all Amphorae assigned to a specific load balancer
that does not have the DELETED status.  This way amphora drivers do not need
to check if the amphora is deleted before operations are attempted.  They can
now just iterate through the existing_amphorae list.

Change-Id: I93ed009a1ff19f54103e9ef571d0f9fa493ed773

commit_message:
remove remaining simplejson uses, prefer standard library import

a1c32702, 736cf54a, and 38787d0f remove uses of `simplejson` from
various parts of Swift in favor of the standard libary `json`
module (introduced in Python 2.6). This commit performs the remaining
`simplejson` to `json` replacements, removes two comments highlighting
quirks of simplejson with respect to Unicode, and removes the references
to it in setup documentation and requirements.txt.

There were a lot of places where we were importing json from
swift.common.utils, which is less intuitive than a direct `import json`,
so that replacement is made as well.

(And in two more tiny drive-bys, we add some pretty-indenting to an XML
fragment and use `super` rather than naming a base class explicitly.)

Change-Id: I769e88dda7f76ce15cf7ce930dc1874d24f9498a

[{'created': '2015-11-16 16:52:01.000000000', 'message': "remove partial upgrade support for nova

Partial upgrade support was a very hacky hybrid state of no stopping
some services so not everything is upgraded to new code levels. Now
that we have a multinode upgrade model in the gate we don't need this
any more, and we should burn this with fire so that more folks don't
go down this path.

Change-Id: I2b1b440aa3cccfb2b72e65e41809c359438024be
"}]
commit_message:
remove partial upgrade support for nova

Partial upgrade support was a very hacky hybrid state of no stopping
some services so not everything is upgraded to new code levels. Now
that we have a multinode upgrade model in the gate we don't need this
any more, and we should burn this with fire so that more folks don't
go down this path.

Change-Id: I2b1b440aa3cccfb2b72e65e41809c359438024be

commit_message:
Upgrade nova's API database during nova upgrade

Nova now has another stream of DB migrations. This patch runs 'sync'
on them as well, right after the main database.

If we're coming from kilo, we need to do the database create part,
as that wasn't run for us in kilo devstack.

Change-Id: If7d8a40cf6faf5740b369487ddcafe9bfd4fdc38

commit_message:
Small fix to yum manual update command

As it was found during testing our official repository isn't
signed with a signature. So 'yum' must be issued with '--nogpgcheck'
in order to update a node correctly.

Change-Id: Ia5c23a498eb7b968d615238fbaa9736d1d2f3344

commit_message:
Change devstack git clone to use https

During devstack stack, Git cloning from Github regularly (not
always) fails using http.
Apparently, Github are moving away from http to https.

MarkMcClain correctly recommends using the devstack variable
GIT_BASE. This is actually a change from http to git protocol.

Track naming change from akanda to astara.

Change-Id: I753fe5edd16f83927993f75ddd29500b01555ea3

commit_message:
Enable listing of role assignments in a project hierarchy

This patch implements the manager and backend support for
listing assignments for a hierarchy. A follow-on patch will
provide the controller level support and rest API.

Implements: bp list-assignment-subtree
Change-Id: Ice6aa85cb012757f326c263de5866537ace99278

commit_message:
Add ngroute libraries to appropriate paths

This patch adds ngroute libraries to appropriate paths and creates an
ng_route_base block in the Django base so templates can insert routing
blocks, such as establishing a base path.

Implements: blueprint add-ngroute
Change-Id: I11dd3890d336f288e93bf884197e3f22dcd1da93

commit_message:
Split v1 shell sub-command into specific files

v1 shell has many sub command. It is difficult to add more test
and functions. Actually we have forgotten to add some tests for
these sub-commands.
This patch splits these.

commit_message:
Add support for rfc7233 range headers.

This is primarily needed by our log_processor gearman workers which currently
attempt to retry failed downloads with partial GETs.

Change-Id: Ic49579d253ea773651e4b9641223c2d2ae961c94

The documentation associated with it can now be removed from
the openstack-manuals page.

commit_message:
Backport TestResource to stable/kilo

The kilo TestResource used in functional tests has limited features and
hidden bugs which are only apparent when other functional tests are
backported. This change backports the stable/liberty TestResource to
stable/kilo.

Change-Id: Ib3648e21440031b0b1231d81a7a2825414457f72
Related-Bug: #1508096

commit_message:
Extract loadbalancer_id from listener create events

We're currently dropping the lb id from listener events, causing
a cache lookup that ends up hitting deleted loadbalancers instead
of the intended one.  This fixes it and looks for loadbalancer_id
in the correct place of listener create events body.

Change-Id: Ic94a8ecbd227d097b25ea004cc8bd7ac76c40580
Closes-bug: #1509595

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-11-05 08:28:54.000000000', 'message': 'Add unit tests for "server pause" command.

In the current osc, we cannot test any interface of a server object.
Because we don't have a Mock object to fake a server.

For example, we cannot test "server pause" command. If we use FakeResource
object to fake a server, just like we did in class TestDeleteServer, we will
run into error because FakeResource object doesn't have a pause() method.
And also, it is not a Mock object.

This patch introduces a new simple class "FakeServer", which is a subclass
of Mock. And then we can use it to test any method of a server object.

And this patch also adds a simple unit test case for "server pause" command
to show how to use this new class.

Change-Id: If5551e77d7dd4f7f48c6ee4a7f80f8313817f492

commit_message:
Add unit tests for "server pause" command.

This patch adds unit tests for "server pause" command,
including one and multiple servers.

Change-Id: If5551e77d7dd4f7f48c6ee4a7f80f8313817f492
Implements: blueprint osc-unit-test-framework-improvement

commit_message:
Introduce random server faking mechanism.

This patch introduces a new server faking mechanism to support
multiple servers faking.

Server names and ids can be generated randomly, and use APIs in
class FakeServer to get one or more servers.

Change-Id: Ic54f3bf7c77294dc7dfb9acdbf4a721eb5eef6af
Implements: blueprint osc-unit-test-framework-improvement

[{'created': '2015-11-11 06:52:45.000000000', 'message': 'Make FakeResource inherit from Mock.

The current unit test framework uses class FakeResource to fake a server,
which inherits from class Object. That means, if we fake a server like this:

server = FakeResource(......)

we cannnot do this kind of call:

server.start(), server.stop(), server.pause(), ......

This is because it is not a Mock instance. This is also the reason why there
is no such test cases in the current osc. This patch make FakeResource inherit
from Mock.

Doing this will bring us two merits:
1. we can test server.xxx() functions
2. we can use Moxk.side_effect to fake multiple servers at one time


NOTE:
1. We should call super.__init__() in the __init__() of FakeResource.
   Otherwise we may occur an error like this: AttributeError: _mock_methods

2. All parameters in __init__() of FakeResource should have default value.
   And it should also take **kwargs parameter. Otherwise Mock will fail to
   get child mock object. Please refer to the following call trace:

    Traceback (most recent call last):
      File "openstackclient/tests/volume/v1/test_volume.py", line 574, in test_volume_list_no_options
        self.assertEqual(datalist, tuple(data))
      File "openstackclient/volume/v1/volume.py", line 314, in <genexpr>
        ) for s in data))
      File "openstackclient/common/utils.py", line 195, in get_item_properties
        data = getattr(item, field_name, '')
      File "/opt/stack/python-openstackclient/.tox/py27/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/mock/mock.py", line 736, in __getattr__
        _new_parent=self
      File "/opt/stack/python-openstackclient/.tox/py27/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/mock/mock.py", line 1023, in _get_child_mock
        return klass(**kw)
    TypeError: __init__() got an unexpected keyword argument '_new_name'

Change-Id: I12eb876cbebab064773df7b5dd612de69bbf3f01
Implements: blueprint osc-unit-test-framework-improvement

commit_message:
Enable FakeResource to fake methods.

Use MagicMock to fake a method in FakeResource. A new function:

    add_method(name, return_value)

is added to FakeResource. The caller specifies method @name and @return_value,
the function will add an attribute with @name, which is a callable MagicMock
object whose return value is @return_value.

When user access the attribute with a (), @return_value will be returned by
MagicMock, which looks like a function call.

Change-Id: I12eb876cbebab064773df7b5dd612de69bbf3f01
Implements: blueprint osc-unit-test-framework-improvement

commit_message:
Support keystone v3 in endpoint creation

In Keystone v3, you make a call per endpoint type, and you get back an
endpoint object for each endpoint type. In keystone v2, you make one call with
all three and each type is a parameter.

Change-Id: Id5bcc6ab0f8f4312947fde72a269867a2903e0a6

commit_message:
Merge keystone.config into keystone.common.config

Having two places for config stuff is confusing. There should only
be the one place for config stuff, keystone.common.config.

Change-Id: I83cae5d2140639df228025851ceb3f90c21af08a

commit_message:
Remove exceed quota will return 413 notification

Nova now don't return HTTP code 413 in case the quota
exceed. so no need to mention this in the doc any more.

Partial-Bug: #1515222

Change-Id: I5b851f01192acfd4bfec7559e38db610a9028c9e

commit_message:
Add a job around using tripleo with docker

The gate is going to test against tripleo patches by deploying
a containerized compute node.

Depends-on: I74da6afbff7de852e8ca946f18d0ad7594b8e551
Change-Id: Ida724d95675bb9aa87f00b9d04e7e344ee3066db

commit_message:
OpenDaylightTestCase replaces sendjson permenently instead of mock

OpenDaylightTestCase replaces OpenDaylightRestClient.sendjson
permanently instead of mocking. which causes subsequent tests failure.
It should be mocked correctly so that it is torn down cleanly.

Change-Id: Ia92be92898c288b555e4d91a02824cc730fdadb2
Closes-Bug: #1517683

commit_message:
Prepare filters for using RequestSpec object

Now that the FilterScheduler is using a RequestSpec object,
we need to change the filters for backporting the object
into the legacy dicts before changing each of them.

Release Notes will be updated to mention that custom filters
need to be modified to either use a RequestSpec object or
primitive them into a dict.

Partially-Implements: blueprint request-spec-object-mitaka

UpgradeImpact - see the reno file attached.

Change-Id: I14f18c4507498b1d24a9318fafc97193861ca0b6

commit_message:
install ebtables locking workaround

ebtables is racing with itself when nova and libvirt attempt to create
rules at the same time in the nat table. ebtables now has an explicit
--concurrent flag, that all tools must opt into to prevent ebtables
from inherently being unsafe to run.

libvirt gained this support in 1.2.11, which is too new for our ubuntu
primary testing environment. Nova still hasn't added this support,
though even if it did, we'd run into the issue with libvirt.

We can do the most ghetto thing possible and create a wrapper for
ebtables that does explicit locking on it's own. It's pretty terrible,
but it should work. And it is the kind of work around that people
unable to upgrade libvirt will probably need to do.

This is an opt in value which we should set in the gate to True.

Related-Bug: #1501558

Change-Id: Ic6fa847eba34c21593b9df86a1c2c179534d0ba5
(cherry picked from commit 7860f2ba3189b0361693c8ee9c65d8d03fb115d6)

commit_message:
Add 'lxd' to the list of recognized hypervisors

Currently its not possible to set the hypervisor_type on a
glance image to 'lxd' to ensure it gets targetted to the
right type of hypervisors as 'lxd' is not a recognised
hypervisor type.

Change-Id: I9607c2f062b5ae19480a92be313fd4e21aa43ca5
Closes-Bug: 1516652

commit_message:
Fix configuration lookup failure

Handle the 'NoSuchOptError' error properly.

NOTE:
This issue was discovered in the MySQLUser model
(although the loaded datastore was not MySQL-related).
It turns out that because MySQL models load
ignored users/dbs into a static field it gets
evaluated very early on module load. The models module however
gets also imported by datastores other than MySQL.
I therefore move the field initialization into the
'__init__' method so that it gets loaded only when needed.

Also added a missing manager name to Postgres calls.

Change-Id: Iea6eb1dd454f55b346b4562ea33dc34243f508ae
Closes-Bug: 1515428

commit_message:
More cleanup of inactive blogs (and images)

In [1] we removed a few blogs that were no longer active and in some
cases generating spam.  This patch removes one more for another
former Citrix employee and also removes the images corresponding
to the people removed in the last patch.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/247520/

Change-Id: Id04aafb25ec7c9169949d65d49424b959dc0acc4

commit_message:
Fix wrong type of exception raised

generate_template and resource_schema methods of service.py
raises wrong type of exceptions after catching them.

Also resource validation failure should not raise stack
validation exception.

Change-Id: I44b8d37db7d2687cee2a7b675dd062b3af3ee167
Closes-Bug: #1447194

commit_message:
Fix broken stable-compat-jobs for oslo

We realized that the new jobs introduced in change
Idcbb3e8c71b0be97c7ab78c426ac363388f46633

was not really testing the master of say oslo.config. The job
was really pulling down the stable/liberty branch. We should fix
this by adding the OVERRIDE flag for just the library under
test.

Change-Id: I372fc1091bbcf1022a4d8d4ae60e65ab67a8e432

Refactor component model

Get rid of component object.
Store info with compatibility and uncompatiblity
lists of components in plugin and release.

Implements: blueprint component-registry

commit_message:
Check for get_quota policy before calling the API

When displaying the "Create Domain" button,
if the user does not have the permission to
get the quota, he would get a warning:
"The quotas could not be retrieved." The warning
shows every time when the user clicks on the Domains
tab and is confusing.

Add a policy check for rule get_quota before
calling the designate quota_get() API and skip
the call if the user does not have the permission.

Change-Id: Ib0a0767b97257f7322ac326c24570a7a4cfc49b7
Closes-Bug: #1513586

commit_message:
Move monasca gate job from experimental to non-voting check job

Running the job automatically as non-voting should give us
more data to fix any remaining problems while providing better
visibility into new errors being introduced.

Change-Id: I5961d6cd9779907ad31409d46577e833af1c028e

commit_message:
swap 3 tempest jobs for 1 layer4 jumbo job

The tempest layer4 job runs all the tests from the heat / sahara /
trove jobs, but in one config. It's run successfully on all the
experimental runs so far.

This will provide us with the same test coverage to ensure these tests
can work on the heat / sahara / trove jobs, but will separate them
from the integrated gate because tempest will now not share a job, by
name, with heat / sahara / trove. It should create faster merge for
all projects because of this with no loss of test coverage.

Change-Id: I34d6427d294cdf82ddf1d4709d3e1630551959f9

commit_message:
[docs] Update Glance architecture image

This patch updates the image located at:
http://docs.openstack.org/developer/glance/architecture.html:

1. glance_store doesn't have authorization, but the authentication
   only.
2. AuthZ -> AuthZ Middleware for clarity.
3. Added an arrow to reflect an optional call from REST API to AuthZ
   Middleware.

Co-Authored-By: Mike Fedosin <mfedosin@mirantis.com>
Co-Authored-By: Olena Logvinova <ologvinova@mirantis.com>

Closes-Bug: #1517849

Change-Id: I695953980a1d717b5b5762b82de24b6e18adde1e

commit_message:
remove use of magic numbers in sql migrate extension tests

There were a few instances of magic numbers being used, declare
them so it's easier to find out why we are using that value.

Change-Id: I175f0a4e1b8f31865da9dd7f24a499cc2075da09

commit_message:
Don't add disabled ipsec connections to pluto

When an ipsec site connection is updated to admin_state_up = False
then its section is removed from ipsec.conf of a vpn service it
belongs to. Due to that attempts to add such connection to pluto
result in failures.

That is why we shouldn't run addconn for connections with
admin_state_up = False. It also makes sense to disable processes
for vpn services which have no enabled ipsec connections.

Change-Id: I1c311a7ee7f2406a09e5c0a9d03413d57aa82534
Closes-Bug: #1507672

commit_message:
Fix H404/405 violations for api tests(1/3)

There is a lot of H404/405 violations in Tempest now, and that leads
difficult to migrate the code to tempest-lib or the other projects'
repos. This patch fixes these violations for api tests except compute
and network.

Change-Id: I783862867732b76d836153bf9ef18fb4a5ec6c6e

commit_message:
Improved test_alarms_state_history

Removed duplicate code (DRY) when creating alarm definitions.

Modified alarms to use the min function to significantly reduce the alarm
state transition times on initialization.

Fixed one small index in an array.

Change-Id: Ie217ab31f664000ae6d4f5c3851755ab8a966f0e

commit_message:
Don't add default route to HA router if there is no gateway ip

When adding an external network with no gateway ip to a HA router,
l3 agent will report exception. The exception comes from the code
of adding default route to HA router. However, if there is no
gateway ip in the external network, there is no need to add such
route.

Change-Id: I41d6a292c903758f408d3d93a64dca7adeeb5769
Closes-Bug: #1515209
(cherry picked from commit 14c09fdfc4fbda874508c170ac6a7d6ead0bfd2e)

commit_message:
Set a default for 'rootwrap_helper_cmd'

The 'rootwrap_helper_cmd' config has no default value set. If it isn't
set to a command, the rootwrap infrastructure won't work. ironic
uses 'sudo ironic-rootwrap', and ironic-rootwrap is the same script as
oslo-rootwrap, so the default is set to 'sudo oslo-rootwrap'.

Change-Id: I1fcf518686b87dd64ed96feaa130af0e3f724c56
Closes-Bug: #1506531

commit_message:
A minor change for driver_shell test

Make mock_client.driver as a Mock of DriverManager.
This will help to avoid mistake like access attributes
not belong to the object.

commit_message:
Adds Magnum Container Network Model to Swarm

1. Updates network-driver API validation.
2. Updates AtomicSwarm template definition for swarm, flannel and
   labels.
3. Adds initial unit test.

Partially-Implements: blueprint extend-baymodel-net-attributes
Partially-Implements: blueprint conductor-template-net-update

Change-Id: Ia80f239bcbd29ae14de25ae3e915a49d9b9bafd1

3. My patch uses etcd :-)

commit_message:
Changes Swarm Bootstrapping from Public to Etcd

Previously, Swarm leveraged Docker's public discovery mechanism
for bootstrapping a cluster. Etcd bootstrapping is supported by
Swarm and is preferred for production use for the following reasons:

1. Required for HA.
2. Is more secure.
3. Required for the Flannel network-driver.

Partially-Implements: blueprint extend-baymodel-net-attributes
Partially-Implements: blueprint conductor-template-net-update

Change-Id: Iab844c03ed7cf8bbee69b72ff71c219f0a5ab1dd

commit_message:
Replace rootwrap_config and rootwrap_helper_cmd with root_helper

ironic-lib will use the command set in the new 'root_helper' conf parameter to execute
commands as root user. If this configuration paramter is not specified,
ironic-lib will execute commands with run_as_root=False. This configuration
is not set by default.

'rootwrap_config' and 'rootwrap_helper_cmd' configs are deleted, since
they are replaced by the new 'root_helper' config.

This fix also delivers a sample ironic-lib.filters file, which should be used
with rootwrap command.

Change-Id: I61ef7c15237c995e9d4cc85095ac48a30a8f6c7d
Closes-bug: #1515943

commit_message:
Fix Rally job for Manila project

One of two Rally jobs for Manila project started failing after change
of logic for share driver that is used in CI job. It started require
wait for init. So, Rally, using old approach did not wait and failed.
So, in Manila was added common bash file for such cases - [1].
Make broken Rally job use common Manila file that will do required
work before allowing run of tests.

[1] I94514405628ab8337d1f4153e431f064614e3596

Change-Id: I9140b0345a88c1f8214e078721812ac9d2012d8e

commit_message:
utils: move code where it's actually used and remove

This patch removes the aodh.utils module by moving the code it contains
where it is actually used.

All the code it contains actually belong to some other places as it's
not shared anymore. This cleans up a bit the code by removing the
module, and makes sure we don't carry dead code in the future.

Change-Id: Ic31aa82d471fc46d64ad546c13f677d897d169d7

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks
    and once the automatic tests pass, it will be reviewed by other friendly
    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. Also it
    takes generally at least a couple of weeks for cores to get around to
    reviewing code. The more you participate in the community the more
    rewarding it is for you. You may also notice that the more you get to know
    people and get to be known, the faster your patches will be reviewed and
    eventually approved. Get to know others and become known by doing code
    reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a great way to learn the code base.

    Thanks again for supporting OpenStack, we look forward to working with you.

    IRC: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/IRC
    Workflow: http://docs.openstack.org/infra/manual/developers.html

commit_message:
Fix missing credentials

A recent tempest commit seems to no longer allow
us to leave credentials as None. This is a quick fix
that will get the credentials and pass them along.

Change-Id: I64e0dbeadbc159d635ea3494e3b77f4ab71644bc

commit_message:
Disable gate-muranoclient-dsvm-functional for kilo and juno

Change I146a5627c640e2ae57437c68ec119489ca6b23f7 made the job voting,
but it was designed for and during liberty and thus it now blocks kilo
and juno gates for muranoclient.
This commit disables the job for those branches

Closes-Bug: #1516099
Change-Id: I1a4fea809fcfd6f0f174d9150134d51766860099

commit_message:
Refactor VPN functional tests to use common template

This will change the existing functional test jobs to use a common job
template. To do this the following steps were taken:

- Make the jobs non-voting, so they don't break the gate. This means
  that reviewers need to check the non-voting results, prior to +A.

- Removed experimental functional jobs that were previously created,
  in neutron-vpnaas repos. These jobs were going to replace the existing
  ones (but do the same thing). Aborting that approach.

- Remove the experimental API job. A separate commit will add it back
  in, and use the new common template, as part of work to getting the
  API job working.

Partial-Bug: #1495584

Change-Id: I015bb7727676a68b1dfc3f04d10a80a308b00435

Preserve data on Ceph OSD devices

ensure that Puppet keeps the existing OSD data set.

commit_message:
Live Migration Automatic Block Migration

https://blueprints.launchpad.net/nova/+spec/live-migration-auto-block-migrate

Currently when doing live migration the end-user must specify whether to
use block migration or not.  This requires them to know whether or not the
instance storage is shared between the compute nodes.  It would be simpler and
more reliable if nova figured this out for itself.

Change-Id: I3c25182cdab757b06c0594c4a67653fb5c8e8a00

commit_message:
Use sudo -H -E when running pip

-E will result in pip writing to the current users disk cache, and
that prevents future non-root pip calls using it properly.

Change-Id: Ib70b3d59a20967bc7e08c70387eb7dd6f7f1b5c5

commit_message:
Allow error status to be specified

For some apis, heat, the error status is "failed". This patch
changes the wait_for_status method to allow for the error
status to be passed in the same way as the success status.

Change-Id: I20db4051d3f5611a4b13fe23ea8798b82a40da81

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-11-06 22:38:33.000000000', 'message': 'Add ability to push images to local registry

This takes advantage of the registry in the undercloud by pulling
necessary images from a specified registry (currently docker.io by
default), tags the images for localhost, and then pushes the images

commit_message:
Add ability to push images to local registry

This takes advantage of the registry in the undercloud by pulling
necessary images from a specified registry (currently docker.io by
default), tags the images for localhost, and then pushes the images
to the local registry.

This will eventually allow the overcloud to pull images locally.

Change-Id: If9cb1c40b8b4ca6e3f2898c1ceb0e690827a904f

[{'created': '2015-10-30 20:26:11.000000000', 'message': "Replace host_alive test with hypervisor VM states

Currently, the host_alive_status metric is a combination of ping tests
and general VM up/down state from the hypervisor isActive().  If ping
tests are not supported in the environment or by the VM's security rules,
host_alive_status becomes practically useless.

This change proposes to make host_alive_status a reliable, stable metric
consisting of one of eight possible status codes, as reported by the
hypervisor, including shut off/paused/suspended, etc.  A value_meta
'detail' tag includes a human-readable translation of the status code,
and the codes are also added to the plugin documentation.

In addition, this change renames the 'ping_only' configuration parameter
to 'alive_only' as a means to gauge the general status of all VMs without
the additional load of performance metrics, for situations where the latter
is overwhelming.  If alive_only is True, only the VM status metrics and
aggregate metrics are published.

The 'ping_status' metric serves as the new name for ping-based testing of
VMs.

commit_message:
Replace host_alive test with hypervisor VM states

Currently, the host_alive_status metric is a combination of ping tests
and general VM up/down state from the hypervisor isActive().  If ping
tests are not supported in the environment or by the VM's security rules,
host_alive_status becomes practically useless.

This change proposes to make host_alive_status a reliable, stable metric
consisting of one of eight possible status codes, as reported by the
hypervisor, including shut off/paused/suspended, etc.  A value_meta
'detail' tag includes a human-readable translation of the status code,
and the codes are also added to the plugin documentation.

In addition, this change renames the 'ping_only' configuration parameter
to 'alive_only' as a means to gauge the general status of all VMs without
the additional load of performance metrics, for situations where the latter
is overwhelming.  If alive_only is True, only the VM status metrics and
aggregate metrics are published.

The 'ping_status' metric serves as the new name for ping-based testing of
VMs.

Change-Id: I77c87b222de0aa9882d1761e8cade87ef1719d7d

commit_message:
Lack of time field caused loss of Alarm History

The time field was name timestamp which caused influxdb to use the
write time for the time field. If multiple Alarm History messages
were written, Influxdb only kept the last because the times were
not unique.

Change-Id: I3808838bb8a26d7a6272ab41c3e586659a037f02

[{'created': '2015-11-04 14:14:15.000000000', 'message': "Squashed commit of the following:

commit 3de128d853903d235747e04754687c5b73834bbd
Author: Swaminathan Vasudevan <swaminathan.vasudevan@hp.com>
Date:   Mon Jun 29 16:19:49 2015 -0700

    Fix update_port_postcommit and port not found with DVR

    Updating DVR Router interface ports was throwing
    errors in the l2pop mechanism drivers function
    update_port_postcommit.

    PortContext's portbinding information does not show
    the status of the ports. For DVR Router interface
    ports the DVRPortbinding table contains the status
    information for the ports.

    In the case of the update_port method, there was
    no code related to DVR that retreives the port
    binding information from the DVRPortBinding table.

    This was working before, since in the driver_context,
    the PortContext was just returning the port status for
    all router interfaces.

    With the recent refactor to the driver_context, this
    behavior changed and the PortContext was returning the
    _binding.status for the DVR router interface ports and
    the _port.status for the non DVR ports.

    When the update_port function calls update_port_postcommit
    with PortContext for DVR router interface ports, l2pop
    was throwing an error saying that Portbinding does not
    have the attribute 'status'.

    This was causing addition of any second subnet to the
    same network with respect to IPv6 to fail.
    Because in the case of IPv6, when you add additional
    subnets to the existing network, it just updates the port
    with the IPv6 prefix instead of creating additional port.

    In the case of IPv4 still we could see that there are
    two different ports created for each subnet we try to
    add.

    This patch fixes the above issue in l2pop and allows the
    DVR router interface ports to be successfull.

    Also the _find_ipv6_router_port_by_network was returning
    all the ports for DVR including the DVR CSNAT internal
    ports which are not part of the router interface ports.

    This patch also fixes this problem by returning false,
    when it finds a DVR SNAT port.

    Closes-Bug: #1465434
    (cherry picked from commit 9eed4167b63f0c0ad6c7ceeedc644e511c8dac75)
    Change-Id: Id243a4b3f30071226411ace6d12550fc099901cc

    Conflicts:
    	neutron/tests/unit/db/test_l3_dvr_db.py

commit 402e1d87e54e7ae4559d6536c941a3cac0304b05
Author: Robert Kukura <kukura@noironetworks.com>
Date:   Wed Apr 1 17:11:59 2015 -0400

    Add unit tests for ML2 DVR port binding and fix PortContext inconsistencies

    Extends the existing ML2 port binding unit tests to cover the
    distributed port bindings used for DVR. Within the test mechanism
    driver, bindings are tracked per-host, and additional assertions are
    added.

    Fixes issues with PortContext attributes that were exposed by these
    new tests. Adds new vif_type, original_vif_type, vif_details, and
    original_vif_details PortContext attributes, similar to the exising
    host, original_host, status, and original_status attributes, to
    reflect host-specific details of distributed (or normal) port
    bindings. Also fixes original_host and original_status to return None
    when in the context of an operation other than an update, and fixes
    original_host to reflect the specific host being bound for a
    distributed port.

    Closes-bug: 1453943
    Closes-bug: 1453955
    Change-Id: I467db0d48e4b82fdaad8d851e294e639a84a8160
    (cherry picked from commit 922dae45d0a223f9256bdff1faa65d469cbc9275)

Change-Id: Ia4ed350dd90e37c5cf2bf1e8635597c8368569cc

commit 3de128d853903d235747e04754687c5b73834bbd
Author: Swaminathan Vasudevan <swaminathan.vasudevan@hp.com>
Date:   Mon Jun 29 16:19:49 2015 -0700

    Fix update_port_postcommit and port not found with DVR

    Updating DVR Router interface ports was throwing
    errors in the l2pop mechanism drivers function
    update_port_postcommit.

    PortContext's portbinding information does not show
    the status of the ports. For DVR Router interface
    ports the DVRPortbinding table contains the status
    information for the ports.

    In the case of the update_port method, there was
    no code related to DVR that retreives the port
    binding information from the DVRPortBinding table.

    This was working before, since in the driver_context,
    the PortContext was just returning the port status for
    all router interfaces.

    With the recent refactor to the driver_context, this
    behavior changed and the PortContext was returning the
    _binding.status for the DVR router interface ports and
    the _port.status for the non DVR ports.

    When the update_port function calls update_port_postcommit
    with PortContext for DVR router interface ports, l2pop
    was throwing an error saying that Portbinding does not
    have the attribute 'status'.

    This was causing addition of any second subnet to the
    same network with respect to IPv6 to fail.
    Because in the case of IPv6, when you add additional
    subnets to the existing network, it just updates the port
    with the IPv6 prefix instead of creating additional port.

    In the case of IPv4 still we could see that there are
    two different ports created for each subnet we try to
    add.

    This patch fixes the above issue in l2pop and allows the
    DVR router interface ports to be successfull.

    Also the _find_ipv6_router_port_by_network was returning
    all the ports for DVR including the DVR CSNAT internal
    ports which are not part of the router interface ports.

    This patch also fixes this problem by returning false,
    when it finds a DVR SNAT port.

    Closes-Bug: #1465434
    (cherry picked from commit 9eed4167b63f0c0ad6c7ceeedc644e511c8dac75)

When testing hiera structures which hasn't
been given values in any of the YAML templates,
defaults must be provided in the noop test
as well. Otherwise there would be errors like:

Failure/Error: configuration_override.fetch(
  'keystone_config', {})
NoMethodError:
  undefined method `fetch' for nil:NilClass

Related blueprint deployment-data-dryrun

Change-Id: Ibe6ffd931d11a2887dba057561f4bd3690eea5c8
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobrelia@mirantis.com>
"}]
commit_message:
Sanitize hiera_structure use in Noop tests

When testing hiera structures which hasn't
been given values in any of the YAML templates,
defaults must be provided in the noop test
as well. Otherwise there would be errors like:

Failure/Error: configuration_override.fetch(
  'keystone_config', {})
NoMethodError:
  undefined method `fetch' for nil:NilClass

Related blueprint deployment-data-dryrun

Change-Id: Ibe6ffd931d11a2887dba057561f4bd3690eea5c8
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobrelia@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
Disable qpid's jobs as it's now deprecated

The qpidd driver has been deprecated in Liberty and it'll be removed in
Mitaka. In order to do this, we need to disable the qpid jobs for
branches newer than Liberty.

Change-Id: If4b1773334e424d1f4a4e112bd1f10aca62682a9

Fix tools/install_pip script

allowing insecure connection to download get-pip.py

commit_message:
Fix a test order issue with oslo_config fixture

The below patch caused a test order issue with the oslo config
override via fixture.  This is causing gate failures.
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/246046/1

This fixes that ordering issue.

Change-Id: Id9390f546cc19ea3af0bfffc0b97b108eb6042e8

commit_message:
Add test coverage for keystone::db::mysql

Currently most of the tests in keystone_db_mysql_spec.rb aren't checking
anything, they're just setting up the framework. This patch will add test
coverage for mysql.

Change-Id: Ieb497d7ebeb0ddc145a53548500b02fbc10399ca

commit_message:
event to sample publisher

Bracket events like compute.instance.create.latency created from BP:
Transformers for events pipeline
https://blueprints.launchpad.net/ceilometer/+spec/events-pipeline-transformers
need to be published and stored as sample.

This spec will add a new notifier publisher that will convert bracket
event to notification, and send the notification back to ceilometer
notification listener, then sample pipeline will convert it to sample.

DocImpact

blueprint event-to-sample-publisher

Change-Id: Ifaab99642eb24fe6a6c056f4093f04705d578518

Use Octavia stable/liberty branch in DevStack README

of the current tags for the DevStack README example.

I could not be happier about this patch in general. I think the stuff about what's in work should not be here- largely because this is a policy document, not documentation on what's up. Perhaps there should be a document like that, which includes longer-form descriptions of what's happening with each of the things as well as forward looking "we'd like to do this" sorts of statements, and this document can clearly state what the Project Policy is on Javascript projects and then link to the other document for a "more information" sort of thing?

OR - maybe not. I like having the document at all more than I feel a need to restructure it - so consider this a soft -1'}, {'account_id': 9717, 'date': '2015-10-12 17:15:57.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

(3 comments)

I'd love a more specific project policy document - something that includes links to, say, a yeoman sample template and other things. To do that, we'd need:

- An appropriate documentation place where "Hey here's how OpenStack does {{language}}" can live.
- Links to that place.

I'm also concerned with the inevitable diaspora of documentation, where one piece lives here, and another lives over there (etc etc), and it's not really easy where to find any of them. Optimally, there'd be One Place (TM) where a new {{language}} engineer can find documentation, faq's, policies, etc, for all things OpenStack {{language}}.

Any suggestions?'}, {'account_id': 16628, 'date': '2015-10-12 17:18:46.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

commit_message:
Added JavaScript to Common Testing Interface

This patch expands the CTI documentation to support multiple
languages. It creates a single page that describes overall CTI goals,
and then links to documents that go into specifics on each language
supported in OpenStack.

The Javascript section is new, and includes documentation for the
current state of the Javascript CTI. It also explicitly calls out
areas where work needs to be done, in order to encourage
discussion and contributions.

Change-Id: I971b9271443e4fd227b4a6b347dfc385b67eb3e4
Depends-On: I00186c9af441c1778a22379634cdb2f918324bd8

commit_message:
Use --concurrent with ebtables

Update our usage of ebtables to pass the --concurrent flag.

With --concurrent ebtables will attempt to acquire a lock file
before making changes. This allows multiple processes, such as
nova an libvirt, to safely access ebtables at the same time.

Support for using --concurrent was added in libvirt 1.2.11, since
we don't know the version of libvirt being used in all
deployments we still retry the ebtables call several times just
in case libvirt isn't using --concurrent.

DocImpact:
 * nova now requires ebtables 2.0.10 or later
 * nova now recommends libvirt 1.2.11 or later

Change-Id: I00ff805cee9653508f013f8aa6d206362ac0f6cb
Partial-Bug: #1501366

commit_message:
Keystone user issues on Puppet Enterprise.

Puppet Enterprise doesn't work for:
 - keystone_user;
 - keystone_tenant;
 - keystone_user_role;

    Error: Could not retrieve catalog from remote server: Error 400 on SERVER: Could not autoload puppet/type/keystone_user: Malformed version number string 3.8.1 (Puppet Enterprise 3.8.1)

This is due to the modified version string that Puppet Enterprise uses.
This patch takes this string into consideration.  It has been tested
successfully on Puppet Enterprise.

Change-Id: I8c79b9331134762620509ca0a6c09e16e534ad9b
Closes-Bug: #1516687

commit_message:
Bay: Update node's ip addresses even bay creation failed

Currently , if bay creation failed, we won't update the node's ip addess to
bay. User won't get the master/node 's ip addresses from bay-show, it's better
to do the update for further debugging.

Remove _create_or_update_complete to _sync_bay_and_template_status and reuse
some existed codes to recude code line number.

Closes-Bug: #1516542
Change-Id: I51438742db9599defb7b9417b84e9f39ab31e4c7

 - change resource names so that autorequire works
 - enable to skip Keystone resource management

commit_message:
Fix notification driver package

In oslo.messaging change:
Ifb96c2ae9868426cac2700bf4917c27c02c90b15

the private package for the messaging driver was changed
to a public package. So we should fix our reference here
in our setup.cfg

Closes-Bug: #1513630

Change-Id: I6b066f4f1b6c6485cb67ca5f8a2a17359521c264
(cherry picked from commit 225663888e71d44e9732951f515da925b8799b74)

commit_message:
Show which breakpoint will be cleared by pressing Enter

It's not that obvious that when being prompted to clear breakpoints, the
last breakpoint in the list is the one that will be cleared if you just
press Enter.

This adds some more text telling the user exactly which breakpoint will
be cleared.

Change-Id: I47dfa5e62fc15f08430c8967895b973a31d7a4e2

commit_message:
Change breakpoint removal log to info

Use LOG.info instead of LOG.warn to log breakpoint removal actions.
Breakpoint removals aren't warnings, especially when we just prompted
the user to remove the breakpoint, there's no point in showing them a
warning that we're removing it.

Change-Id: I7ee8ed2675c4072b70cd04e592e0d6ba51350e01

Ryan McNair: "This all looks good - I'm just missing how this relates to the randomized hashing, could you enlighten me on that?"

Try to run the test on Python 2 with -R command line option, we will see tests failing without this change.

The representation of a dictionary depends on the order on how items are stored in the internal structure ("buckets"). The order depends on the hash function, which is now randomized. In short, repr(dict) is randomized.

Example:

 $ python3 -c 'print(repr({"a": 1, "b": 2}))'
 {'a': 1, 'b': 2}
 $ python3 -c 'print(repr({"a": 1, "b": 2}))'
 {'b': 2, 'a': 1}

Currently, the test relies on the exact representation of dictionaries. With my change, I check the dictionary (keys+values) instead of its repr(). In fact, some tests already checked the dict keys+values, but not all of them.'}, {'account_id': 9107, 'date': '2015-11-06 11:17:47.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

(2 comments)

> What is the difference between repr and Comment() ?

commit_message:
Modify test_hpe3par to support random hash

On Python 3, or on Python 2 with -R command line option, the hash
function is now randomized for security. Changes:

* Rename CommentMatcher to Comment and simplify it.
* Generalize the usage of Comment.

Change-Id: I0233bab571aee3c034f067e6c28e6b38dc017db9

commit_message:
remove bad entry point test logic

The test being removed verifies that stevedore and pkg_resources work as
expected, and enforce an import scheme through the getattr calls that
should be left up to the plugin definition and not hard-coded into the
tests.

Change-Id: I7ccc0a624e3822de1ea6864f49a254c80a35ae53

commit_message:
[WIP] Add support of multiple vif_types to mech driver

Add new VIFDriverBase abstract class. This class has 3 methods:
- is_supported: check if the agent suppports this vif driver
- get_vif_type: return the vif_type of the vif_driver
- get_vif_details: return the vif_details of the vif_driver

The SimpleAgentMechanismDriverBase is modified to:
- add a list of VIF drivers in the attribute.
- the __init__ method instances a default VIFDriver. The default
  VIFDriver needs to be always at the end of the vif_drivers list.
- the try_to_bind_segment_for_agent method iterates on the vif_drivers
  list until it find one supported by the agent (i.e is_supported method).
  This vif driver is used to get the vif_type and vif_details.

The ovs ML2 mechanism driver is updated to use this new framework:
- Add a new DpdkOvsVIFDriver class heriting of VIFBaseDriver.
- Add an instance of DpdkOvsVIFDriver to the vif_driver list

This commit also add a unit test for ovs ML2 mech driver for the ovs
dpdk case.

Change-Id: I2bccbf9e52cd11a76e7ae366a4b17be06c5c7232
Signed-off-by: Maxime Leroy <maxime.leroy@6wind.com>

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be

    eventually approved. Get to know others and become known by doing code

commit_message:
tox.ini: check migrations for the subproject only

There is no need to check all migrations from all installed migration
entrypoints available on the system as part of pep8 check.

Change-Id: Id2ca40eb7a287d0919dac8e98801cc2324873a25
(cherry picked from commit 73abc7887b9b94d72272a0e58d0e7cddefe0e26d)

commit_message:
Check for existence of network group when uploading template

Network groups can be created at any time so there is no guarantee
that it will exist when a template is uploaded. Before updating the
network group's VLAN the existence of the network group is checked.

Networks are reassigned for all nodes when a new network group is
created. A new pre-deployment check was added to validate that all
network groups required by a network template exist.

Change-Id: I28d3df4db0fe69f5b4fc9af491f0aae1f695901f
Closes-bug: #1509543

commit_message:
Update neutron_service_names variable get method

Using service_name as neutron services program name in
playbooks/roles/os_neutron/tasks/neutron_upstart_init.yml,
like the follow format:
program_name: "{{ neutron_services['neutron-l3-agent'].service_name }}"

And neutron_service_names variable is used in playbooks/roles/
os_neutron/handlers/main.yml.

So we need to keep consistent about neutron service names.

Change-Id: I61dba2b49cb3f69443e53b4efb76f06e0cd1a47e

On my undercloud VM (with 8G ram, 2G free) building overcloud-full
always fails unless this is set, so make a best effort to figure out
a sane setting by looking at the free memory.  4G is a guess, but it's

commit_message:
Set DIB_NO_TMPFS when image building without much RAM

On my undercloud VM (with 8G ram, 2G free) building overcloud-full
always fails unless this is set, so make a best effort to figure out
a sane setting by looking at the free memory.  4G is a guess, but it's
better than always failing with 2G and gfidente mentioned on IRC 12G
VMs work OK.

Change-Id: I8998b1eb3e4fb0a51183f25aacaab7819f4b1854

commit_message:
Enable no-redeclare

Disallow Redeclaring Variables (no-redeclare)

In JavaScript, it's possible to redeclare the same variable name
using var. This can lead to confusion as to where the variable is
actually declared and initialized.

http://eslint.org/docs/rules/no-redeclare

Change-Id: I0ef2febe67700532d748327f9a0f10f846c7ae80

commit_message:
Remove some old no-longer-relevant entries

John doesn't work at Citrix anymore, and the old link is now spamming
the planet. Eric doesn't work at cloudscaling anymore. And bcwaldon.cc
isn't even a website.

commit_message:
WIP - Experimental Agent Pool Manager Backend

*Adds a PM backend to call into the Agent
*Pool Manager will error if Creates/Deletes fail in the Agent
*Adds a terrible hack to let you NOTIFY the agent/poll Bind9
**That will go away when Pool Manager "Targets" come about

Change-Id: I390dbc5130eee40fb1bebae5666472f105ba2438

commit_message:
vmware: check for response body in error conditions

The response may not have a body in certain error conditions, like
a 500 on a socket error as seen in the VMware NSX CI. This fixes
an AttributeError when trying to access the response body in those
cases.

Change-Id: I086bb5bdb59813d326d45b5f7545da2ebb12aa95
Closes-Bug: #1517275

commit_message:
Update requirements to suit the existence of lxc vg

If lxc volume group exists, the aio will try to use
this volume group to create the containers.

As one container will use a hard 5GB of storage, and
the fact that (by default) there is more than 16
containers, you'll exhaust all your storage space
and the aio build will fail.

This commit should make this failure more clear to
openstack-ansible users.

The amount of disk is counted with the default
install.

Change-Id: I84f68a24423f9e7046b1235ef51bf2291708fcec

commit_message:
Add unit tests for cmd/house_keeping

So far we don't have unit tests for method house_keeping_db_cleanup,
,spare_amphora_check and main in file cmd/house_keeping.py,
this patch is to add unit tests for these 3 methods.

Change-Id: I2f45b905d96a883b364e7645eeac0a7b8a1e9aba

I'd like to let at least one more person, especially, Lakshmi take a look before bumping up to +2 though.

Aside from some of my original comments, there are some bigger things on my mind which relate to both the notification forwarding BP as well as the future concept of search syntax negotiation.  One hint at that is the notion of abstracting the data enrichment processing (having to do callbacks to get more data) from the actual serialization / formatting for the data.

commit_message:
Restructure index and notification classes

This patch is open for review, but may need further revision.

Some functionality related to notifications lives in the plugin base
class whereas it should belong to the notification handler base.
This patch refactors all existing plugins and the base class. It adds
a configuration option 'notifications_topic' to the top level
'resource_plugin' group, and a multivalued
'notifications_topic_exchanges' option to each plugin in the case for
where services use different topics from one another.

Change-Id: Ib11f9f46f1624939287f0a74a4a508fce477b319
Closes-Bug: #1515028

commit_message:
change port option from Opt to IntOpt

this change alleviates the warning produced by oslo-config-generator
from the port option by incorporating the integer minimum and maximum
into the configuration option.

Change-Id: Icd14219f86a00666af2f8ef6ac00d8fbf31d1676
Closes-Bug: #1517211

commit_message:
Bump oslo.config >=2.7.0

neutron wants to use max_length argument in StrOpt added in
oslo.config 2.7.0 to remove a neutron-specific option definition.

Change-Id: Id3a3189cb6845e3f9dfb145fd8e067753c5a128a

docs: update the API faults concept guide

This updates the API concept guide to talk about request-ids
and the Server Actions API, while keeping the existing content
on sync and async errors.

Nova v2 API code handle Invalid exception at boot API,
and due to a lot of exception inherit from Invalid, we
should catch and handle it at last of the server create
try/catch flow to make sure we won't return 500 error
in such case.

Compute API will call function
https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/master/nova/compute/api.py#L544
this in turn will call
https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/master/nova/image/api.py#L91
which will call
https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/master/nova/image/glance.py#L290
then finally
https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/master/nova/image/glance.py#L621
may raise exception.Invalid

Change-Id: Ia6ec5c561706c75e06b356993f8bc722109ed9e7
Related-bug: 1483645
"}, {'created': '2015-11-12 12:43:20.000000000', 'message': 'Change Invalid exception to a specified exception

Compute API will call function
https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/master/nova/compute/api.py#L544
this in turn will call
https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/master/nova/image/api.py#L91
which will call
https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/master/nova/image/glance.py#L290
then finally
https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/master/nova/image/glance.py#L621
may raise exception.Invalid

so nova need to catch that exception and handle it, instead of using
Invalid exception to catch unexpected exception, use a new exception
for this kind of error case and catch it at API layer.

Change-Id: Ia6ec5c561706c75e06b356993f8bc722109ed9e7
Related-bug: 1483645

Invalid exception to catch unexpected exception, use a new exception
for this kind of error case and catch it at API layer.

commit_message:
Change Invalid exception to a specified exception

Compute API will call function
https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/master/nova/compute/api.py#L544
this in turn will call
https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/master/nova/image/api.py#L91
which will call
https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/master/nova/image/glance.py#L290
then finally
https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/master/nova/image/glance.py#L621
may raise exception.Invalid

so nova need to catch that exception and handle it, instead of using
Invalid exception to catch unexpected exception, use a new exception
for this kind of error case and catch it at API layer.

Change-Id: Ia6ec5c561706c75e06b356993f8bc722109ed9e7
Related-bug: 1483645

commit_message:
Add some tests for map_dev

Ensure that nova.virt.disk.mount.api.Mount.map_dev attempts to map a
device according to the device name and partition supplied.

Change-Id: I593f153575c77b73d187c704b87ee16094a6ada6
Partial-Bug: #1428639

Fix a spelling mistake in the log

be 'vcpu'.

commit_message:
Remove deprecated use_namespaces option

use_namespace option has been removed from neutron so we can cleanup
neutron-fwaas.

Closes-Bug: #1508188
Depends-On: I2fbf65df1250d9f9f1656b3964ee3b6de1ef1118

commit_message:
Remove deprecated use_namespaces option

The use_namespaces option has been defined as a workaround to kernels
not properly supporting namespaces. This limitation is behind us, it's
time to remove use_namespaces after its deprecation in Kilo in order to
simplify code and remove a poorly tested case (use_namespaces=False).

This change prepares for removal pullup_route method[1] which was only
used when use_namespaces=False.

[1] neutron.agent.linux.ip_lib

DocImpact
UpgradeImpact
Closes-Bug: #1508188
Related-Bug: #1435382
Depends-On: I303038eec560a6d99421140c2822aed8b518470b
Depends-On: I4feb2a15c7e1e4bfdbed2531b18b8e7d798ab3cc
Change-Id: I2fbf65df1250d9f9f1656b3964ee3b6de1ef1118

  Python 3, the hash function is randomized by default.

  version. Before, the comparison between mock.Mock and int raised a
  TypeError.
* tox.ini: add test_hp3par to Python 3.4

commit_message:
Port HP 3PAR driver to Python 3

* Use oslo_serialization.base64.encode_as_text() to get Unicode on
  Python 3.
* Replace sys.maxint with sys.maxsize, sys.maxint was removed in
  Python 3.
* test_hpe3par: use list(set()) to get FCWWNs is the right order. On
  Python 3, the hash function is randomized by default.
* test_hpe3par: fix client getWsApiVersion() to return a valid
  version. Before, the comparison between mock.Mock and int raised a
  TypeError.
* hpe_3par_common: set version to 3.0.2
* hpe_3par_iscsi: set version to 3.0.1
* tox.ini: add test_hpe3par to Python 3.4

Partial-Implements: blueprint cinder-python3
Change-Id: I2bed171c0db93b8ea83127a69a63c3bb2317b10b

commit_message:
virt: add constraint to handle realtime policy

This commit makes pinning constraints to take into
account of new introduced option cpu_realtime.
It verifiy if the configuration is good or raise an
error to user.

Change-Id: Iefbb60fcc4f8d1a4b6f8ca8bac9c9a0d8bec3a62
Blueprint: libvirt-real-time

commit_message:
Raise error when node was not found in nailgun

For improving logging and avoiding TypeError we should raise an error
here in case when a slave wasn't added to nailgun database.

Change-Id: Iaff6e6844a1e76fe0f292ff82be1d4cf083e946a
Closes-bug:#1517034
